@vrothberg they're already in a pod. i'm developing mailman to launch with podman in a pod. i have a container in that pod called mailman-core which hosts the REST api. I need to update that with a new image, you can see it here. I'm testing a new image.

https://github.com/maxking/docker-mailman/pull/617/commits/82e6bc15bb6a7694b1c83b982d21ccd78fe2aa4f#diff-cf59feb0a11b2f24b23d39c055b50ef5bf0713b5abd0e9c2496548e55a8c7237R23

However, [mailman-web requires mailman-core](https://github.com/maxking/docker-mailman/pull/617/commits/82e6bc15bb6a7694b1c83b982d21ccd78fe2aa4f#diff-cf59feb0a11b2f24b23d39c055b50ef5bf0713b5abd0e9c2496548e55a8c7237R54) and because of this I can not run mailman-core on a new image without first removing mailman-web.
